<title>Gentoo Security</title>
<section>
<title>Libxml2 URI Parsing Buffer Overflow Vulnerabilities</title>
<body>
<p>

    A buffer overflow has been discovered in libxml2 versions prior to
    2.6.6 which may be exploited by an attacker allowing the execution of
    arbitrary code.
  
</p>
<p>
For more information, please see the <uri link="http://www.gentoo.org/security/en/glsa/glsa-200403-01.xml">GLSA Announcement</uri>
</p>
</body>
</section>
<section>
<title>Linux kernel do_mremap local privilege escalation vulnerability</title>
<body>
<p>

    A critical security vulnerability has been found in recent Linux kernels
    by Paul Starzetz of iSEC Security Research which allows for local privilege escalations.
  
</p>
<p>
For more information, please see the <uri link="http://www.gentoo.org/security/en/glsa/glsa-200403-02.xml">GLSA Announcement</uri>
</p>
</body>
</section>
